Step 1: Determine the Accounts Receivable at the beginning and at the end of the period from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Accounts Receivable = 0.00  
• Ending Accounts Receivable = 1,502,354.84  

Step 2: Compute the average Accounts Receivable:  
 Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) / 2  
  = (0.00 + 1,502,354.84) / 2  
  = 751,177.42

Step 3: From the income statement, the Main Business Revenue (which we will assume to be equivalent to credit sales for this calculation) is 5,565,589.48.

Step 4: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio:  
 Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 5,565,589.48 / 751,177.42  
  ≈ 7.41

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 7.41.
